        "body": "Process multiple requests efficiently using async/await for better performance.",
        "code_snippet": "import asyncio\n\nasync def process_batch(prompts):\n    tasks = [client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-3-sonnet\",\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \n                  \"content\": p}]\n    ) for p in prompts]\n    return await asyncio.gather(*tasks)"
